"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence submitted by the Department of Health (AMR0043)&#xa0;Introduction\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;How has antimicrobial resistance developed in the past decade? \n&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;What are the gaps in our knowledge about antimicrobial resistance? \n&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nMulti Drug Resistant BacteriaMetricKlebsiella - carbapenem\n% non-susceptible to imipenem &amp;/or meropenem\nE. coli\n - cephalosporin\n% non-susceptible to cefotaxime &amp;/or\n&#xa0;\nceftazidime\nE. coli\n - fluoroquinolone\n% non-susceptible to ciprofloxacin\nPseudomonas - carbapenem\n% non-susceptible to imipenem &amp;/or meropenem\nN. gonorrhoeae\n - ceftriaxone\n% non-susceptible\nKlebsiella - cephalosporin\n% non-susceptible to cefotaxime &amp;/or ceftazidime\nPseudomonas - cephalosporin\n% non-susceptible to ceftazidime\nE. coli\n - gentamicin\n% non-susceptible\nS. pneumoniae\n - penicillin\n% non-susceptible\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Is there sufficient research and investment into new antibiotics or other treatments and methods to ensure continued protection against infection?  If not, how could this be rectified?\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;What measures (including behavioural change) have been most effective in controlling the spread of resistant pathogens, and could such measures be used to control other pathogens? \n&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nBehaviour change and AMR \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;What global coordination and action is required to fight antimicrobial resistance and is the UK contributing enough towards cross-border initiatives?\n&#xa0;&#xa0;\nRaising the international profile of AMR\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nThe pipeline of new antibiotics and novel treatments\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWhat are the strengths and weaknesses of the Government’s 2013-2018 Strategy for tackling antimicrobial resistance? What changes might be made to further strengthen the Government’s action plan?\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nNovember 2013\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n \nhttp://www.who.int/mediacentre/factsheets/fs194/en/\nh\nttp://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130107105354/http:/www.dh.gov.uk/prod_consum_dh/groups/dh_digitalassets/@dh/@en/documents/digitalasset/dh_4078448.pdf\n \nhttp://www.who.int/drugresistance/WHO_Global_Strategy_English.pdf\n \nhttps://www.gov.uk/government/publications/chief-medical-officer-annual-report-volume-2\n \nGram-negative bacteria\n are \nbacteria\n that retain \ncrystal violet\n dye in the \nGram staining\n protocol, and are associated with resistance against antibiotics.\n \nhttps://www.gov.uk/government/publications/uk-5-year-antimicrobial-resistance-strategy-2013-to-2018\n \nhttp://www.hpa.org.uk/Publications/InfectiousDiseases/Tuberculosis/1308TBintheUK2013report/\n Gonorrhoea is a sexually acquired infection caused by the bacterium \nNeisseria gonorrhoeae\n.\n \nData drawn from the following sources:\n·\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n Past and current population estimates for England: \nhttp://nww.indicators.ic.nhs.uk/webview/\n; \n·\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n ONS population projections from HSCIC population statistics database: \nhttps://login.hscic.gov.uk/Login.aspx?version=4&amp;referrer=http%3a%2f%2fmy.hscic.gov.uk%2f&amp;info=http%3a%2f%2fmy.hscic.gov.uk%3a80%2fSignIn.htm\n·\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n PHE Mandatory Surveillance Database of Healthcare Associated Infections.\nDH query on the period January 2011 to September 2013.\n&#xa0;\n \n·\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n Residential Care:\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n \nhttp://www.lse.ac.uk/LSEHealthAndSocialCare/pdf/Dilnot_report.pdf\n; \n&#xa0;\n \nhttp://www.nice.org.uk/media/842/61/HCAIQualityImprovementGuide.pdf\n \nhttp://www.nice.org.uk/nicemedia/live/13683/58591/58591.pdf\n \nhttp://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/77376/1/9789241504485_eng.pdf\n More information on ESPAUR is available at \nhttp://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24027247\n These were set out at annex C of the UK Five Year Antimicrobial Resistance Strategy (2013).\n \n2012-2017\n \nThese figures do not include investment in wider underpinning research which is important for increasing knowledge of the basic biology of the organisms or hosts. However the EPSRC data does include investment in developing epidemiological models of infectious diseases, techniques to diagnose and monitor infectious disease and novel antimicrobial therapeutics/agents in response to drug resistance.\n&#xa0;\n See Pharmatimes, September 2013\n UK Five Year Antimicrobial Resistance Strategy; page 16 -20 (2013).\n \nhttp://jac.oxfordjournals.org/content/66/suppl_2/ii41.full\n \nhttps://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-health-and-social-care-act-2008-code-of-practice-on-the-prevention-and-control-of-infections-and-related-guidance\n.\n \nhttp://www.his.org.uk/files/3813/7088/0820/4_epic2_National_Evidence-Based_Guidelines_for_Preventing_Healthcare-Associated_Infections_in_NHS_Hospitals_in_England_2007.pdf\n&#xa0;\n \nhttps://www.gov.uk/government/publications/antimicrobial-stewardship-start-smart-then-focus\n Prevention and control of infection in care homes - an information resource\nhttps://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/214929/Care-home-resource-18-February-2013.pdf\n&#xa0;\n Antimicrobial prescribing and stewardship competences.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n Advisory Committee on Antimicrobial Resistance and Healthcare Associated Infections and Public Health England.\n&#xa0;\n (Se